\n!Position\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Darya Klishina]]\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's long jump|Long jump]]\n|6.64 \n|8  '''q'''\n|6.63\n|9\n|}\n\n==Badminton==\n{{main article|Badminton at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussia has qualified four badminton players for each of the following events into the Olympic tournament. [[Vladimir Vadimovich Malkov|Vladimir Malkov]] and Natalia Perminova were selected among the top 34 individual shutlers each in the men's and women's singles, while London 2012 Olympians [[Vladimir Ivanov (badminton)|Vladimir Ivanov]] and [[Ivan Sozonov]] secured the men's doubles spot by virtue of their top 16 finish in the Badminton World Federation World Rankings as of 5 May 2016.<ref>{{cite news|first=Dev|last=Sukumar|title=Provisional List of Olympic Qualifiers Published|url=http://bwfbadminton.com/2016/05/05/provisional-list-of-olympic-qualifiers-published/|publisher=[[Badminton World Federation]]|date=5 May 2016|accessdate=5 May 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508130917/http://bwfbadminton.com/2016/05/05/provisional-list-of-olympic-qualifiers-published/|archivedate=8 May 2016}}</ref> On 28 July 2016, BFW cleared all four athletes for competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newsfirst.lk/english/2016/07/russian-badminton-cleared-rio-olympics/143070|title=Russian badminton cleared for Rio Olympics \u2013 Newsfirst|last=|first=|date=28 July 2016|website=|publisher=|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729152335/http://newsfirst.lk/english/2016/07/russian-badminton-cleared-rio-olympics/143070|archive-date=29 July 2016|access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Athlete\n!rowspan=2|Event\n!colspan=4|Group Stage\n!Elimination\n!Quarterfinal\n!Semifinal\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vladimir Vadimovich Malkov|Vladimir Malkov]]\n|align=left|[[Badminton at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's singles|Men's singles]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Nguy\u1ec5n Ti\u1ebfn Minh|Nguy\u1ec5n T M]]|VIE|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' (21\u201315, 9\u201321, 13\u201321)\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Lin Dan|Lin D]]|CHN|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' (18\u201321, 7\u201321)\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[David Obernosterer|Obernosterer]]|AUT|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' (21\u201311, 21\u201310)\n|3\n|colspan=5| Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vladimir Ivanov (badminton)|Vladimir Ivanov]]<br />[[Ivan Sozonov]]\n|align=left|[[Badminton at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's doubles|Men's doubles]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Lee Sheng-mu|Lee S-m]] / <br />[[Tsai Chia-hsin|Tsai C-h]]|TPE|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' (21\u201311, 22\u201320)\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Matthew Chau|Chau]] / <br />[[Sawan Serasinghe|Serasinghe]]|AUS|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' (21\u201316, 21\u201316)\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Lee Yong-dae|Lee Y-d]] / <br />[[Yoo Yeon-seong|Yoo Y-s]]|KOR|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' (21\u201317, 19\u201321, 21\u201316)\n|1 '''Q'''\n|{{n/a}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Chai Biao|Chai B]] / <br />[[Hong Wei|Hong Wi]]|CHN|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' (13\u201321, 21\u201316, 16\u201321)\n|colspan=3| Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Natalia Perminova]]\n|align=left|[[Badminton at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's singles|Women's singles]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Elisabeth Baldauf|Baldauf]]|AUT|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' (21\u201317, 21\u20138)\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Tai Tzu-ying|Tai T-y]]|TPE|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' (12\u201321, 9\u201321)\n|{{n/a}}\n|2\n|colspan=5| Did not advance\n|}\n\n==Boxing==\n{{main article|Boxing at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussia has entered eleven boxers to compete in the following weight classes into the Olympic boxing tournament. [[Vladimir Nikitin (boxer)|Vladimir Nikitin]] and Adlan Abdurashidov were the only Russians finishing among the top two of their respective division in the World Series of Boxing, while three further boxers (Aloyan, Zamkovoy, and Chebotarev) did so in the AIBA Pro Boxing Series.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sovsport.ru/news/text-item/775252|script-title=ru:\u0411\u043e\u043a\u0441\u0435\u0440 \u041c\u0438\u0448\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u043e\u044f\u043d \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043b \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u043c \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043c \u043e\u043b\u0438\u043c\u043f\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u0443\u0442\u0435\u0432\u043a\u0438 \u0432 \u0420\u0438\u043e- 2016|trans-title=Boxer Misha Aloyan becomes the first Russian winner to secure a ticket for Rio 2016|language=ru|publisher=[[Sovetsky Sport]]|accessdate=30 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924142253/http://www.sovsport.ru/news/text-item/775252|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Vasily Yegorov]], [[Vitaly Dunaytsev]], and [[Evgeny Tishchenko]] had claimed their Olympic spots at the [[2015 AIBA World Boxing Championships|2015 World Championships]].<ref>{{cite news|title=First 60 boxers from 24 countries confirmed for Rio 2016 as early Olympic quota places taken up|url=http://www.aiba.org/blog/first-60-boxers-24-countries-confirmed-rio-2016-early-olympic-quota-places-taken/|publisher=[[International Boxing Association (amateur)|AIBA]]|date=10 December 2015|accessdate=10 December 2015}}</ref>\n\nYaroslava Yakushina and Anastasia Belyakova were the only two Russian women to book their Olympic spots with a semifinal victory at the [[2016 European Boxing Olympic Qualification Tournament|2016 European Qualification Tournament]] in [[Samsun]], Turkey, and with a quarterfinal victory at the [[2016 AIBA Women's World Boxing Championships|Women's World Championships]] in [[Astana]], Kazakhstan, respectively.<ref>{{cite news|title=Azerbaijan\u2019s Yana Alekseevna delivers an inspired performance as Europe\u2019s top boxers book places at Rio 2016|url=http://www.aiba.org/blog/azerbaijans-yana-alekseevna-delivers-an-inspired-performance-as-europes-top-boxers-book-places-at-rio-2016/|publisher=[[International Boxing Association (amateur)|AIBA]]|date=16 April 2016|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref> Meanwhile, Petr Khamukov secured an additional place on the Russian roster with his quarterfinal triumph at the [[2016 AIBA World Olympic Qualifying Tournament|2016 AIBA World Qualifying Tournament]] in [[Baku]], Azerbaijan.<ref>{{cite news|title=World Olympic Qualifier Quarter-Finals see Haiti, Iraq, Tajikistan and Turkmenistan among 23 nations to confirm quota places at Rio 2016|url=http://www.aiba.org/blog/world-olympic-qualifier-quarter-finals-see-haiti-iraq-tajikistan-turkmenistan-among-23-nations-confirm-quota-places-rio-2016/|publisher=[[International Boxing Association (amateur)|AIBA]]|date=24 June 2016|accessdate=24 June 2016}}</ref> All of the boxers were cleared for competition one day prior to the opening ceremony.<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/36970627|title=Rio 2016: Russian boxers cleared to compete at Olympic Games|last=|first=|date=4 August 2016|website=BBC|publisher=|access-date=4 August 2016}}</ref>  However, Tishchenko's final match and Nikitin's quarterfinal match became controversial, leading to the suspension of the referees in question, with many observers saying that Tishchenko\u2019s and Nikitin\u2019s opponents were robbed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/olympics/la-sp-oly-rio-2016-controversial-decisions-lead-to-1471450461-htmlstory.html|accessdate=17 August 2016|publisher=[[Los Angeles Times]]|title=Controversial decisions lead to suspension of boxing judges}}</ref>  Nikitin was forced to withdraw from his semifinal bout against [[Shakur Stevenson]] due to cuts he sustained in his previous bouts; he received a bronze medal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Rio 2016 Olympics boxing: Russia\u2019s Nikitin out, USA\u2019s Stevenson receives bye into gold medal fight|url=http://www.badlefthook.com/2016/8/18/12531820/rio-2016-olympics-boxing-russia-s-nikitin-out-usa-s-stevenson-receives-bye-into-gold-medal-fight|publisher=Bad Left Hook|accessdate=18 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 December 2016 [[Misha Aloyan]] was found to have committed an anti-doping rule violation after testing positive for Tuaminoheptane, a specified stimulant, prohibited in-competition under S6 on the WADA Prohibited List, during an in-competition doping control on 21 August 2016. The results obtained by the athlete in the Rio 2016 Olympic Games were disqualified.<ref name=\"tas-cas.org\"/>\n\n;Men\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Round of 32\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!colspan=2|Final\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vasily Yegorov]]\n|align=left|[[Boxing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's light flyweight|Light flyweight]]\n| {{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Nico Hern\u00e1ndez|Hern\u00e1ndez]]|USA|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 0\u20133\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center \n|align=left|'''[[Misha Aloyan]]'''\n|align=left|[[Boxing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's flyweight|Flyweight]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Elie Konki|Konki]]|FRA|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 3\u20130\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ceiber \u00c1vila|\u00c1vila]]|COL|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''W''' 3\u20130\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Hu Jianguan|Hu Jg]]|CHN|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''W''' 3\u20130\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Shakhobidin Zoirov|Zoirov]]|UZB|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 0\u20133\n|{{abbr|DSQ|Disqualified}}\n|-align=center\n|align=left|'''