a}}\n|3000\n|13\n|}\n\n==Fencing==\n{{main article|Fencing at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussian fencers have qualified a full squad each in the men's team foil, women's team \u00e9p\u00e9e, and women's team sabre by virtue of their top 4 national finish in the FIE Olympic Team Rankings, while the men's \u00e9p\u00e9e team has claimed the spot as the highest ranking team from Europe outside the world's top four.<ref>{{cite news|first=Darci|last=Miller|title=U.S. Women's Saber Team Qualifies For Rio|url=http://www.teamusa.org/News/2016/February/02/US-Womens-Saber-Team-Qualifies-For-Rio|publisher=[[United States Olympic Committee|Team USA]]|date=2 February 2016|accessdate=4 February 2016}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, 2012 Olympic bronze medalist [[Nikolay Kovalev (fencer)|Nikolay Kovalev]] and three-time Olympian [[Aleksey Yakimenko]] (men's sabre), along with women's foil fencers [[Inna Deriglazova]] and [[Aida Shanaeva]], had claimed their individual spots on the Russian team by finishing among the top 14 in the FIE Adjusted Official Rankings.<ref>{{cite news|title=Russia top as Olympic qualification by ranking ends|url=http://rio2016.fie.org/media/news/view-news/1337|publisher=[[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale d'Escrime|FIE]]|date=5 April 2016|accessdate=6 April 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160417101111/http://rio2016.fie.org/media/news/view-news/1337|archivedate=17 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe fencing team was officially named to the Olympic roster on 17 June 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tass.ru/sport/3371516|script-title=ru:\u0422\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0440: \u043a\u0430\u0436\u0434\u044b\u0439 \u0438\u0437 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0444\u0435\u0445\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u044c\u0449\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0439\u043d\u043e \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043d\u0430 \u041e\u0418-2016|trans-title=Coach: Each of the Russian fencers can adequately perform at the 2016 Olympics|language=ru|publisher=[[Russian News Agency TASS]]|date=17 June 2016|accessdate=19 June 2016}}</ref> In regard to the doping scandal, the [[F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale d'Escrime|International Fencing Federation]], cleared all Russian fencers for competition.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n;Men\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n!rowspan=2|Athlete\n!rowspan=2|Event\n!Round of 64\n!Round of 32\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinal\n!Semifinal\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|- style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vadim Anokhin]]\n|align=left rowspan=3|[[Fencing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's \u00e9p\u00e9e|\u00c9p\u00e9e]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Maxime Brinck-Croteau|Brinck-Croteau]]|CAN|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 15\u201314\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Max Heinzer|Heinzer]]|SUI|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 7\u201315\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Anton Avdeev]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Bas Verwijlen|Verwijlen]]|NED|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 15\u20139\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Kazuyasu Minobe|Minobe]]|JPN|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 12\u201315\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Pavel Sukhov]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Park Sang-young|Park S-y]]|KOR|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 11\u201315\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Vadim Anokhin]]<br />[[Anton Avdeev]]<br />[[Sergey Khodos]]<br/>[[Pavel Sukhov]]\n|align=left|[[Fencing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team \u00e9p\u00e9e|Team \u00e9p\u00e9e]]\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCteam|UKR|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 32\u201345\n|''Classification semifinal''<br/>{{flagIOCteam|SUI|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 28\u201345\n|''7th place final'