35\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Charlotte Lembach|Lembach]]|FRA|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 15\u201314\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[C\u00e9cilia Berder|Berder]]|FRA|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 15\u201310\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Manon Brunet|Brunet]]|FRA|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 15\u201314\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Yana Egorian|Egorian]]|RUS|2016 Summer}}<br />'''L''' 14\u201315\n|{{silver02}}\n|- align=center\n|align=left|'''[[Yekaterina Dyachenko]]<br/>[[Yana Egorian]]<br />[[Yuliya Gavrilova]]<br />[[Sofiya Velikaya]]'''\n|align=left|[[Fencing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team sabre|Team sabre]]\n|colspan=3 {{n/a}}\n|{{flagIOCteam|MEX|2016 Summer}}<br /> '''W''' 45\u201331\n|{{flagIOCteam|USA|2016 Summer}}<br /> '''W''' 45\u201342\n|{{flagIOCteam|UKR|2016 Summer}}<br />'''W''' 45\u201330\n|{{gold01}}\n|}\n\n== Golf ==\n{{main article|Golf at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussia has entered one golfer into the Olympic tournament. [[Maria Verchenova]] (world no. 338) qualified directly among the top 60 eligible players for their respective individual events based on the IGF World Rankings as of 11 July 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Olympic Rankings \u2013 Women|url=http://www.igfgolf.org/olympic-games/qualification-system/ogr-women/|publisher=[[International Golf Federation]]|date=11 July 2016}}</ref> On 4 August 2016, Verchenova was cleared to participate in the competition.<ref name=\":11\" />\n\n{|class=wikitable style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Athlete\n!rowspan=2|Event\n!Round 1\n!Round 2\n!Round 3\n!Round 4\n!colspan=3|Total\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Score\n!Score\n!Score\n!Score\n!Score\n!Par\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Maria Verchenova]]\n|align=left|[[Golf at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's individual|Women's]]\n|75\n|70\n|73\n|62\n|280\n|\u22124\n|=16\n|}\n\n== Gymnastics ==\n{{main article|Gymnastics at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\n\n===Artistic===\nRussia fielded a full squad of five gymnasts in both the men's and women's artistic gymnastics events through a top eight finish each in the team all-around at the [[2015 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships]] in [[Glasgow]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Louise|last=Radnofsky|title=U.S. Women Gymnasts Qualify for Rio Olympics, Though in Mixed Fashion|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-women-gymnasts-qualify-for-rio-olympics-though-in-mixed-fashion-1445729014|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=24 October 2015|accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Will |last=Graves |title=U.S. Men Off to Solid Start in World Gymnastics Qualifying |url=http://universalsports.com/2015/10/26/u-s-men-off-to-solid-start-in-world-gymnastics-qualifying/ |publisher=[[Universal Sports Network]] |date=26 October 2015 |accessdate=27 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151027170454/http://universalsports.com/2015/10/26/u-s-men-off-to-solid-start-in-world-gymnastics-qualifying/ |archivedate=27 October 2015 }}</ref> The men's and women's gymnastics squads, led by London 2012 uneven bars champion [[Aliya Mustafina]] and bronze medalists [[Denis Ablyazin]] and [[Maria Paseka]], were named to the Olympic roster at the Russian Cup in [[Penza]] on 3 July 2016.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ru:\u041e\u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0438\u043c\u043d\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u041e\u0418-2016|trans-title=Russia announces the gymnastics teams for the 2016 Olympics|url=http://tass.ru/sport/3426733|language=ru|publisher=[[Russian News Agency TASS]]|date=3 July 2016|accessdate=4 July 2016}}</ref> The [[International Federation of Gymnastics]] cleared all Russian gymnasts to compete.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n;Men\n;Team\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=3|Athlete\n!rowspan=3|Event\n!c