m air rifle]]\n|629.0\n|2 '''Q'''\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|184.2\n|{{bronze03}}\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vasily Mosin]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's double trap|Double trap]]\n|132\n|13\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Fedor Vlasov]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 50 metre rifle three positions|50 m rifle 3 positions]]\n|1176\n|6 '''Q'''\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|403.1\n|7\n|}\n\n;Women\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!colspan=2|Qualification\n!colspan=2|Semifinal\n!colspan=2|Final\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Points\n!Rank\n!Points\n!Rank\n!Points\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Tatiana Barsuk]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's trap|Trap]]\n|62\n|18\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left rowspan=2|'''[[Vitalina Batsarashkina]]'''\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air pistol|10 m air pistol]]\n|390\n|1 '''Q'''\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|197.1\n|{{silver02}}\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 25 metre pistol|25 m pistol]]\n|578\n|13\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left rowspan=2|[[Ekaterina Korshunova]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air pistol|10 m air pistol]]\n|387\n|2 '''Q'''\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|73.5\n|8\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 25 metre pistol|25 m pistol]]\n|582\n|8 '''Q'''\n|16\n|5\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Ekaterina Rabaya]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's trap|Trap]]\n|65\n|11\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Albina Shakirova]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's skeet|Skeet]]\n|69\n|7\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left rowspan=2|[[Daria Vdovina]]\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle|10 m air rifle]]\n|417.4\n|4 '''Q'''\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|143.5\n|5\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle three positions|50 m rifle 3 positions]]\n|579\n|15\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|}\n<small>Qualification Legend: '''Q''' = Qualify for the next round; '''q''' = Qualify for the bronze medal (shotgun)</small>\n\n==Swimming==\n{{main article|Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussian swimmers have so far achieved qualifying standards in the following events (up to a maximum of 2 swimmers in each event at the Olympic Qualifying Time (OQT), and potentially 1 at the Olympic Selection Time (OST)):<ref>{{cite web|title=Swimming World Rankings |url=http://www.fina.org/H2O/index.php?option=com_wrapper&view=wrapper&Itemid=805 |publisher=[[FINA]] |accessdate=14 March 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110106131744/http://www.fina.org/H2O/index.php?option=com_wrapper&view=wrapper&Itemid=805 |archivedate= 6 January 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Rio 2016 \u2013 FINA Swimming Qualification System |url=http://www.fina.org/H2O/docs/events/rio2016/2014-07%20-%20Rio%202016%20-%20Qualification%20System%20-%20FINAL%20-%20Swimming%20-%20EN.pdf |format=[[PDF]] |work=[[Rio 2016]] |publisher=[[FINA]] |accessdate=23 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221025939/http://www.fina.org/H2O/docs/events/rio2016/2014-07%20-%20Rio%202016%20-%20Qualification%20System%20-%20FINAL%20-%20Swimming%20-%20EN.pdf |archivedate=21 February 2015 }}</ref> To assure their selection to the Olympic team, swimmers must finish in the top two of each individual event with the federation's corresponding standard slightly faster than the FINA A-cut at the Russian Championships & Olympic Trials ( 16 to 23 April) in [[Moscow]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.swimmingworldmagazine.com/news/previews-of-upcoming-olympic-qualifying-meets-from-around-the-world/|title=Previews Of Upcoming Olympic Qualifying Meets From Around The World|publisher=[[Swimming World Magazine]]|date=4 April 2016|accessdate=5 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nA total of 37 swimmers (24 men and 13 women) were selected to the Russian roster for the Olympics, including London 2012 medalists [[Anastasia Valeryevna Zuyeva]], [[Yuliya Yefimova]], and [[Vladimir Morozov (swimmer)|Vladimir Morozov]], and 2014 Youth Olympic backstroke champion [[Evgeny Rylov]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vesti.ru/doc.html?id=2746589&cid=680|script-title=ru:\u0415\u0444\u0438\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0432\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u043f\u043b\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044e|trans-title=Efimova is not included in the preliminary list for the Russian national swimming team|language=ru|publisher=[[Vesti (VGTRK)|Vesti]]|date=24 April 2016|accessdate=25 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 July 2016, [[FINA]], following the guidelines set out by the International Olympic Committee, announced that seven swimmers declared by the [[Russian Olympic Committee]] for the Rio games were deemed ineligible \u2013 four, Mikhail Dovgalyuk, [[Yuliya Yefimova]], [[Nataliya Lovtsova]] and Anastasiya Krapyvina, because of previous doping bans, and three, [[Nikita Lobintsev]], [[Vladimir Morozov (swimmer)|Vladimir Morozov]] and [[Daria Ustinova]], because of being implicated in the 'disappearing positive methodology' uncovered by the McClaren report. The status of relay teams involving these ineligible swimmers remained unclear.<ref>{{cite news|title=PR 64 \u2013 FINA STATEMENT \u2013 Participation of Russia at the Rio 2016 Olympic Games|url=http://fina.org/news/pr-64-fina-statement-%E2%80%93-participation-russia-rio-2016-olympic-games|publisher=[[FINA]]|accessdate=25 July 2016}}</ref> On 4 August 2016, Morozov and Lobintsev were reported to be cleared for participation by the IOC.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://swimswam.com/morozov-lobintsev-approved-rio-olympics-tass-reports/ |title=Morozov, Lobintsev Approved For Rio Olympics, TASS Reports |first1=Jared |last1=Anderson |date=4 August 2016 |publisher=Swimswam |accessdate=4 August 2016 }}</ref> On 5 August 2016, the date of the opening ceremony, Yuliya Yefimova, Natalya Lovtsova, Daria Ustinova, Mikhail Dovgalyuk, and Anastasiya Krapyvina were cleared for participation.<ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=http://tass.ru/en/sport/892815|title=279 Russian athletes cleared to compete in Rio Olympics|date=6 August 2016|publisher=[[Russian News Agency TASS]]|accessdate=6 August 2016}}</ref> Consequently, all of the declared Russian swimmers were allowed to participate.\n\n;Men\n{|class=wikitable style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!colspan=\"2\"|Heat\n!colspan=\"2\"|Semifinal\n!colspan=\"2\"|Final\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Time\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Vyacheslav Andrushenko]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 400 metre freestyle|400 m freestyle]]\n|3:50.23\n|30\n|colspan=2 {{n/a}}\n|colspan=2|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Aleksei Brianskiy]]\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 50 metre freestyle|50 m freestyle]]\n|22.33\n|28\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|'''[[Anton Chupkov]]'''\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 200 metre breaststroke|200 m breaststroke]]\n|2:07.93 '''[[List of Russian records in swimming|NR]]'''\n|1 '''Q'''\n|2:08.08\n|6 '''Q'''\n|2:07.70 '''[[List of Russian records in swimming|NR]]'''\n|{{bronze03}}\n|-align