u0432 \u0433\u0440\u0443\u043f\u043f\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u041e\u0418-2016|trans-title=Russia names the synchronized swimming team for the 2016 Olympics|language=ru|url=http://tass.ru/sport/3431557|accessdate=6 July 2016|publisher=[[Russian News Agency TASS]]|date=6 July 2016}}</ref> The team was cleared to compete one day prior to the opening ceremony.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://olympics.cbc.ca/news/article/russian-boxers-canoeist-cleared-compete-rio.html|title=Russian athletes learn Rio Olympic fate|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804153449/http://olympics.cbc.ca/news/article/russian-boxers-canoeist-cleared-compete-rio.html|archive-date=4 August 2016|access-date=4 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!colspan=2|Technical routine\n!colspan=3|Free routine (preliminary)\n!colspan=3|Free routine (final)\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Points\n!Rank\n!Points\n!Total (technical + free)\n!Rank\n!Points\n!Total (technical + free)\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|'''[[Natalia Ishchenko]]<br>[[Svetlana Romashina]]'''\n|align=left|[[Synchronized swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's duet|Duet]]\n|96.4577\n|1 \n|98.0667\n|194.5244\n|1 '''Q'''\n|98.5333\n|194.9910\n|{{gold01}}\n|-align=center\n|align=left|'''[[Vlada Chigireva]]<br>[[Natalia Ishchenko]]<br>[[Svetlana Kolesnichenko]]<br>[[Aleksandra Patskevich]]<br>[[Elena Prokofyeva]]<br>[[Svetlana Romashina]]<br>[[Alla Shishkina]]<br>[[Gelena Topilina]]<br>[[Maria Shurochkina]]'''\n|align=left|[[Synchronized swimming at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team|Team]]\n|97.0106\n|1\n|colspan=3 {{n/a}}\n|99.1333\n|196.1439 \t\n|{{gold01}}\n|}\n\n==Table tennis==\n{{main article|Table tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nRussia has entered three athletes into the table tennis competition at the Games. 2012 Olympian [[Alexander Shibaev (table tennis)|Alexander Shibaev]] and Polina Mikhailova secured an Olympic spot each in the men's and women's singles, respectively, by winning their respective group final match at the European Qualification Tournament in [[Halmstad]], [[Sweden]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Ian |last=Marshall |title=Once Again an Olympian, Panagiotis Gionis Books Place in Memorable Style |url=http://www.ittf.com/_front_page/ittf_full_story1.asp?ID=43996&Competition_ID=2631& |publisher=[[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]] |date=14 April 2016 |accessdate=15 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507210132/http://www.ittf.com/_front_page/ittf_full_story1.asp?ID=43996&Competition_ID=2631& |archivedate= 7 May 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Ian |last=Marshall |title=Defensive Skills Secure First Ever Olympic Places for Han Ying and Polina Mikhailova |url=http://www.ittf.com/_front_page/ittf_full_story1.asp?ID=43994&Competition_ID=2631& |publisher=[[International Table Tennis Federation|ITTF]] |date=14 April 2016 |accessdate=15 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416210000/http://www.ittf.com/_front_page/ittf_full_story1.asp?ID=43994&Competition_ID=2631& |archivedate=16 April 2016 }}</ref> Meanwhile, Maria Dolgikh granted a wildcard invitation from [[International Table Tennis Federation]]  to compete in the women's singles as one of the next seven highest-ranked eligible players, not yet qualified, on the Olympic Ranking List. In regard to the doping issue, the ITTF cleared all three athletes to compete.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.com/tennis/russian-table-tennis-trio-take-deep-breath-reaching-rio_sto5703173/story.shtml|title=Russian table tennis trio take deep breath reaching Rio|last=|first=|date=30 July 2016|website=|publisher=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802194211/http://www.eurosport.com/tennis/russian-table-tennis-trio-take-deep-breath-reaching-rio_sto5703173/story.shtml|archive-date=2 August 2016|access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Athlete\n!rowspan=2|Event\n!Preliminary\n!Round 1\n!Round 2\n!Round 3\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|- style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Rank\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Alexander Shibaev (table tennis)|Alexander Shibaev]]\n|align=left|[[Table tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's singles|Men's singles]]\n|colspan=2 {{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jakub Dyjas|Dyjas]]|POL|2016 Summer}}<br>'''W''' 4\u20130\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Timo Boll|Boll]]|GER|2016 Summer}}<br>'''L''' 3\u20134\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Maria Dolgikh]]\n|align=left rowspan=2|[[Table tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's singles|Women's singles]]\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Lay Jian Fang|Lay J F]]|AUS|2016 Summer}}<br>'''L''' 3\u20134\n|colspan=7|Did not advance\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Polina Mikhailova]]\n|colspan=2 {{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Viktoria Pavlovich|Pavlovich]]|BLR|2016 Summer}}<br>'''L''' 2\u20134\n|colspan=6|Did not advance\n|}\n\n==Taekwondo==\n{{main article|Taekwondo at the 2016 Summer Olympics}} \nRussia entered three athletes into the taekwondo competition at the Olympics. 2012 Olympic bronze medalists [[Aleksey Denisenko]] and [[Anastasia Baryshnikova]] and newcomer [[Albert Gaun]] qualified automatically for their respective weight classes by finishing in the top 6 [[World Taekwondo Federation]] Olympic rankings.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.worldtaekwondofederation.net/first-wave-of-24taekwondo-athletes-qualifies-for-2016-rio-olympics/|title=First Wave of 24 Taekwondo Athletes Qualifies for 2016 Rio Olympics|publisher=[[World Taekwondo Federation]]|date=6 December 2015|accessdate=7 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.worldtaekwondofederation.net/second-tranche-of-24-taekwondo-athletes-earn-berths-to-rio-olympics-on-day-2-of-grand-prix-final-egypt-iran-china-and-korea-grab-golds/|title=Second Tranche of 24 Taekwondo Athletes Earn Berths to Rio Olympics On Day 2 of Grand Prix Final, Egypt, Iran, China and Korea Grab Golds|publisher=[[World Taekwondo Federation]]|date=7 December 2015|accessdate=7 December 2015}}</ref> In regard to doping, all of the athletes were cleared to compete.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!Repechage\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|-style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Opposition<br />Result\n!Rank\n|-align=center\n|align=left|'''[[Aleksey Denisenko]]'''\n|align=left|[[Taekwondo at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 68 kg|Men's \u221268 kg]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Edgar Contreras (taekwondo)|Contreras]]|VEN|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''W''' 12\u20132\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Servet Tazeg\u00fcl|Tazeg\u00fcl]]|TUR|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''W''' 19\u20136 {{abbr|PTG|Decision by points gap}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jaouad Achab|Achab]]|BEL|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''W''' 6\u20131\n|{{n/a|Bye}}\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ahmad Abu-Ghaush|Abu-Ghaush]]|JOR|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''L''' 6\u201310\n|{{silver02}}\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Albert Gaun]]\n|align=left|[[Taekwondo at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 80 kg|Men's \u221280 kg]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Steven L\u00f3pez|L\u00f3pez]]|USA|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''L''' 4\u20137\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|-align=center\n|align=left|[[Anastasia Baryshnikova]]\n|align=left|[[Taekwondo at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 67 kg|Women's \u221267 kg]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Rabia G\u00fcle\u00e7|G\u00fcle\u00e7]]|GER|2016 Summer}}<br/>'''L''' 8\u20139\n|colspan=5|Did not advance\n|}\n\n==Tennis==\n{{main article|Tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics}}\nLondon 2012 silver medalist [[Maria Sharapova]] was ruled ineligible to compete at the Games, as the [[International Tennis Federation]] ordered her a two-year suspension for testing positive in the banned substance [[meldonium]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://espn.go.com/tennis/story/_/id/16044538/maria-sharapova-suspended-two-years-international-tennis-federation-positive-drug-test-meldonium|title=Maria Sharapova suspended 2 years over positive doping test|date=9 June 2016|publisher=[[ESPN]]|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nRussia has entered eight tennis players (two men and six women) into the Olympic tournament. [[Andrey Kuznetsov (tennis)|Andrey Kuznetsov]] (world no. 42) and [[Evgeny Donskoy]] (world no. 77) qualified directly for the men's singles as two of the top 56 eligible players in the [[ATP Entry Ranking|ATP]] World Rankings, while [[Svetlana Kuznetsova]] (world no. 12), [[Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova]] (world no. 23), [[Daria Kasatkina]] (world no. 31), and [[Ekaterina Makarova]] (world no. 36) did so for the women's singles based on their [[Women's Tennis Association|WTA]] World Rankings as of 6 June 2016.\n\nHaving been directly entered to the singles, Kuznetsova and Makarova also opted to play with their partners [[Margarita Gasparyan]] and [[Elena Vesnina]], respectively, in the women's doubles, by virtue of the former's top-10 WTA ranking on the list.<ref name=\":11\">{{cite news|url=http://www.itftennis.com/news/232270.aspx|title=ITF announces updated entries for Rio 2016 Olympics|publisher=[[International Tennis Federation]]|date=30 June 2016|accessdate=1 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|script-title=ru:\u0428\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0432\u043e\u0448\u043b\u0430 \u0432 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u041e\u0418-2016|trans-title=Sharapova did not become part of the Russian tennis team for the 2016 Olympics|language=ru|url=http://www.mk.ru/sport/2016/06/27/sharapova-ne-voshla-v-sostav-sbornoy-rossii-na-oi2016.html|publisher=[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]|date=27 June 2016|accessdate=3 July 2016}}</ref> Due to the withdrawal of several tennis players from the Games, [[Teymuraz Gabashvili]] (world no. 96) received a spare ITF Olympic place to join Donskoy and Kuznetsov in the men's singles.\n\nOn 14 July 2016, Gasparyan withdrew from the Olympics due to injury and was replaced with Kasaktina to be partnered with Kuznetsova.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.championat.com/tennis/news-2519430-myskina-hoteli-chtoby-na-igrah-sygral-duet-kuznecovagasparjan-no-u-rity-travma.html|title=\u041c\u044b\u0441\u043a\u0438\u043d\u0430: \u0445\u043e\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0438, \u0447\u0442\u043e\u0431\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0445 \u0441\u044b\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043b \u0434\u0443\u044d\u0442 \u041a\u0443\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0446\u043e\u0432\u0430/\u0413\u0430\u0441\u043f\u0430\u0440\u044f\u043d, \u043d\u043e \u0443 \u0420\u0438\u0442\u044b \u0442\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043c\u0430 [Myskina: wanted the Games played a duet Kuznetsova/Gasparyan, but Rita injury]|publisher=championat.com|language=Russian|date=14 July 2016|accessdate=31 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 July 2016, the [[International Tennis Federation]] announced that the eight players competing for Russia had been deemed eligible.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itftennis.com/news/234939.aspx|title=Statement of the ITF on Russian participation in the Rio 2016 Games|date=24 July 2016|publisher=[[International Tennis Federation]]|accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/29/sports/olympics/international-tennis-federation-russia-doping.html|title=Tennis Was Ready to Act on Russian Eligibility for Rio|last=Rothenberg|first=Ben|date=28 July 2016|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=2 August 2016}}</ref> On 4 August 2016, the IOC cleared all of the players to participate.<ref name=\":10\" />\n\n;Men\n{|class=wikitable style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Round of 64\n!Round of 32\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|- style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Evgeny Donskoy]]\n|align=left rowspan=3|[[Tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's singles|Singles]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jan-Lennard Struff|Struff]]|GER|2016 Summer}}<br>'''W''' 6\u20133, 6\u20134\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[David Ferrer|Ferrer]]|ESP|2016 Summer}}<br>'''W''' 3\u20136, 7\u20136<sup>(7\u20131)</sup>, 7\u20135\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Steve Johnson (tennis)|Johnson]]|USA|2016 Summer}}<br>'''L''' 1\u20136, 1\u20136\n|colspan=4|Did not advance\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Teymuraz Gabashvili]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Radu Albot|Albot]]|MDA|2016 Summer}}<br>'''L''' 6\u20134, 4\u20136, 4\u20136\n|colspan=6|Did not advance\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Andrey Kuznetsov (tennis)|Andrey Kuznetsov]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Roberto Bautista Agut|Bautista Agut]]|ESP|2016 Summer}}<br> '''L''' 7\u20136<sup>(7\u20134)</sup>, 2\u20136, {{abbr|ret|Retired}}\n|colspan=6|Did not advance\n|}\n\n;Women\n{|class=wikitable style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Athlete\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Event\n!Round of 64\n!Round of 32\n!Round of 16\n!Quarterfinals\n!Semifinals\n!colspan=2|Final / {{abbr|BM|Bronze medal match}}\n|- style=\"font-size:95%\"\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Opposition<br />Score\n!Rank\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Daria Kasatkina]]\n|align=left rowspan=4|[[Tennis at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's singles|Singles]